  "local_port": 60664,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I print an application form on the OJAS website?",
  "response": "OJAS, which stands for Online Job Application System, is used by the Gujarat government in India for recruiting into various posts. If you need to print an application form from the OJAS website, you can follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Visit the OJAS Website:**\n   Go to the official OJAS website by typing \"ojas.gujarat.gov.in\" in your web browser.\n\n2. **Navigate to My Application:**\n   On the homepage, look for a section or tab that says \"My Application\" or something similar. This is where you will find your submitted applications.\n\n3. **Login to Your Account:**\n   You may need to log in using your credentials (such as your registration number and password). Ensure you have these details handy.\n\n4. **Find Your Application:**\n   Once logged in, you should see a list of applications you have submitted. Look for the specific application form you wish to print.\n\n5. **Print Your Application Form:**\n   - Locate the application you want to print.\n   - There should be a \"Print\" icon or a \"Print Application\" option next to your application form.\n   - Click on the print option. This might download a PDF version of the form or directly open it in a printable format.\n\n6. **Use the PDF Viewer/Printer:**\n   - If the form opens as a PDF, use the print function in your PDF viewer (such as Adobe Acrobat Reader).\n   - Make sure your printer is connected and select the appropriate printer and settings.\n\n7. **Alternative Option:**\n   If there is no direct print option, you might need to open the application first to view details and then use your browser\u2019s print function (Ctrl + P on Windows or Command + P on Mac).\n\n8. **Contact Support (if needed):**\n   If you face any issues, the OJAS website typically has contact information or a help section where you can seek assistance.\n\nAlways ensure you are using the official and secure version of the website and avoid sharing personal details unnecessarily.",
